msgstr "&erik.kjaer.pedersen.role;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:17
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "Bzip2 is a compression program"
msgid "<command>bzip2</command> is a compression program."
msgstr "Bzip2 er et komprimeringsprogram."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:19
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The bzip2 kioslave is not directly usable, and is intended for use as a "
#| "filter. For example, the tar kioslave can filter a file through the bzip2 "
#| "kioslave, in order to display the contents of a <literal role=\"extension"
#| "\">tar.bz2</literal> file directly in a &konqueror; window."
msgid ""
"The bzip2 KIO worker is not directly usable, and is intended for use as a "
"filter. For example, the tar KIO worker can filter a file through the bzip2 "
"KIO worker, in order to display the contents of a <literal role=\"extension"
"\">tar.bz2</literal> file directly in a &konqueror; window."
msgstr ""
"bzip2-kioslaven kan ikke bruges direkte, men er beregnet til brug som et "
"filter. For eksempel, kan tar kioslaven filtrere en fil gennem bzip2-"
"kioslaven, for at vise indholdet af en  <literal role=\"extension\">tar.bz2</"
"literal>-file direkte i et &konqueror; vindue."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:25
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If you click on a file compressed with a <literal role=\"extension\">."
#| "bz2</literal> in &konqueror;, this kioslave is used to uncompress it and "
#| "display it as a normal (uncompressed) file."
msgid ""
"If you click on a file compressed with a <literal role=\"extension\">.bz2</"
"literal> in &konqueror;, this KIO worker is used to uncompress it and "
"display it as a normal (uncompressed) file."
msgstr ""
"Hvis du klikker på en fil med <literal role=\"extension\">.bz2</literal> i "
"&konqueror;, bruges denne kioslave til at dekomprimere den og vise den som "
"en normal (ukomprimeret) fil."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:29
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If you are a developer, and would like to use the bzip2 filter, you can "
#| "find documentation on using kioslaves at <ulink url=\"http://developer."
#| "kde.org\">http://developer.kde.org</ulink>"
msgid ""
"If you are a developer, and would like to use the bzip2 filter, you can find "
"documentation on using KIO workers at <ulink url=\"http://techbase.kde.org"
"\">http://techbase.kde.org</ulink>"
msgstr ""
"Hvis du er udvikler, og gerne vil bruge bzip2-filtret, kan du finde "
"dokumentation om brug af kioslaver på <ulink url=\"http://developer.kde.org"
"\">http://developer.kde.org</ulink>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:33
#, no-c-format
msgid "See the manual: <ulink url=\"man:/bzip2\">bzip2</ulink>."
msgstr "Se manualen: <ulink url=\"man:/bzip2\">bzip2</ulink>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:36
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>bzip</command> is the ancestor of bzip2. It is rarely used today, "
"having been replaced with bzip2, which offers much better compression."
msgstr ""

#~ msgid "bzip2"
#~ msgstr "bzip2"
